{
  "stem": "12904.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when I was still living in Chicago, working in Chicago before I joined the service, I was going around collecting for a bomber from a German-Jewish refugees.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Got enough money together to buy a bomber to bomb Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had thought of myself as a pacifist.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother had thought of herself as a pacifist, but under the circumstances we gave up being pure pacifists because we felt that Hitler had to go and so that had to be stopped.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I have said to a lot of people, a lot of my friends are pacifists, that I can't be that anymore, pure pacifist.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I feel we have a right to defend ourselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I see.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You told me an interesting narrative that I'd like you to reprise if you don't mind about a return to Stuttgart in 1967.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My first time, after both my parents had died, and I had been divorced-- my second husband-- I went back to-- in 1967.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was 30 years after I had-- I had left Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said, I finally found the courage to return to my, quote, 'fatherland,' my homeland, in my old hometown, Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was an attempt to go home to find myself after going through a divorce and experiencing the death of both parents within three months of each other.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I felt the need-- I won't read everything on that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was one classmate I write about who I could not find her, who had sent flowers to the ship, to the boat what we left on the for me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was not-- she was not a close friend, but I couldn't find her because she probably had married or moved away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Couldn't find a name.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
